South Africa’s rand firmed early on Monday, hurdling the key technical level of R14.50 on its way to a one-year best as signs of a local economic rebound and continued stimulus in the United States lifted demand for the currency. At 0700 GMT, the rand was 0.5% firmer at R14.47 per dollar, a touch off the session best of R14.46 which is its strongest since January 2020. Subscribe for full access to all our share and unit trust data tools, our award-winning articles, and support quality journalism in the process. You will be redirected to a checkout page.
